<div class="jumbotron" ng-app="hello">
  <header>
    <h1>Exercise2: You will be practising creating modules and controllers</h1>
  </header>
  <div class="main-container" ng-controller="StringGameController">
    <div class="row">
      <h3>Convert the solution from Exercise 1 to a more modular code</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>create a file named student.js in the public/assets/js folder</li>
        <li>create a module named 'hello'</li>
        <li>add a controllers constructor function named 'StringGameController' to the module using the controller() method</li>
        <li>Write the relevant code in the StringGameController to perform the concatenation and adjust the view accordingly</li>
        <li>include the student.js file in exercise_2.html.erb</li> 
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="form-group row">
      <div class="col-md-5">
        <label for="firstString">First String</label>
        <input type="string" class="form-control" id="firstString" ng-model="firstString">
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-5">
        <label for="secondString">Second String</label>
        <input type="string" class="form-control" id="secondString" ng-model="secondString">
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Concatenating {{firstString}} with {{secondString}} results in {{concatenate()}}</p>
  </div>
</div>